/api/v2/copilot/models.get: List Copilot models, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.

/api/v2/experiments.get: Lists all experiments that belong to a user across all projects.

/api/v2/groupsquota.get: Return all the groups and its quotas based on the context. Admin gets all the groups details.

/api/v2/jobs.get: Returns all jobs a user has access to.

/api/v2/models.get: List all models that belong to a user across all projects.

/api/v2/newsfeeds/{category}.get: List the newsfeeds, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.

/api/v2/projectnames.get: Return all the project names the user has access to, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.

/api/v2/projects.get: Return all projects, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.

/api/v2/projects/batch.get:
Return a list of projects given a list of project IDs. This method will only return
projects that the calling user has access to, and can be used in situations where
information about a subset of projects (like project names) is needed.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/applicatio.get: List applications, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.
/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/applicatio.post: Create an application and implicitly start it immediately.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/experiment.get: List all experiments in a given project.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/experiment.delete: Delete an experiment that belongs to an experiment id.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/experiment.get: Returns a list of Runs that belong to an experiment.
/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/experiment.post: Create a run for an experiment.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/experiment.get:
Get metadata, metrics, params, tags and artifacts for a run. In the case where multiple metrics
with the same key are logged for a run, return only the value with the latest timestamp.
If there are multiple values with the latest timestamp, return the maximum of these values.
Gets the all the recorded metrics for the key for a given run.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/experiment.post: Bulk delete an experiment run details like metrics, params, tags in one request.
Bulk update an experiment run details like metrics, params, tags in one request.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/files/{pat.get: List files/subdirectories at a specified path
/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/files/{pat.patch: Update file metadata, such as renaming.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/jobs.get: Returns all jobs, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/jobs/{job_.get: Lists job runs, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.
/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/jobs/{job_.post: Create and start a new job run for a job.
Stops a job run. Encoded as a custom method.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/models.get: List models, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/models/{mo.get: List model builds, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.
List model deployments, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.

/api/v2/registry/models/{model_id}.delete: Unregister a model deletes a model.

/api/v2/runtimeaddons.get: List the available runtime addons, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.

/api/v2/runtimes.get: List the available runtimes, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.
/api/v2/runtimes.post: Register a runtime, given the URL to the image in the docker registry

/api/v2/runtimes:update.post: Update the status of selected runtimes

/api/v2/runtimes:validate.get: Validate a runtime, given the URL to the image in the docker registry

/api/v2/ts_data.get: Return the time series data for the requested resource or property.

/api/v2/usage.get: Return the new usage view based on the caller context, optionally filtered, sorted, and paginated.

/api/v2/users/{user_id}.get: Lists user details for specified user id.

/api/v2/usersquota.get: Return all the user names and quotas based on the context. Admin gets all the users details.

/api/v2/projects/{project_id}/files.post: upload a file as a multi-part upload

/api/v2/runtimeaddons/custom.post: Create a new Custom Runtime Addon from an uploaded tarball
